<?php

/**
 * @file
 * Install / uninstall hooks for supplier_price_ingest.
 *
 * Phase 3.1 — both hooks intentionally empty.
 *
 * Why install() is empty:
 *   All schema additions in this phase are config-driven (entity types,
 *   bundles, field storages, field instances, displays, pathauto
 *   patterns, permissions) and ride in via `drush cim` from the YAMLs
 *   shipped in config/sync/. There is no install-time data seed, no
 *   programmatic field creation, and no migration step.
 *
 * Why uninstall() is empty (and especially: why field_replaced_by stays
 * on uninstall):
 *   - The three new ECK entity types (supplier_price_ingest_batch,
 *     supplier_price_ingest_row, supplier_ingest_config) are owned by
 *     ECK + their own config; they are removed by config sync when their
 *     bundle YAMLs leave config/sync/, not by this module's uninstall.
 *   - field_replaced_by lives on the material entity, not on any entity
 *     owned by this module. It is not module-owned; it must NOT be
 *     deleted on this module's uninstall. The field is also expected to
 *     accumulate data over time (the apprentice's catalog cleanup
 *     surfaces values into it) and that data must survive an
 *     uninstall/reinstall of the ingest pipeline.
 *   - field_ingest_batch on material_price_history.entry is module-
 *     adjacent (it references this module's batch entity type). If this
 *     module is uninstalled, existing history rows that reference a
 *     batch should retain the reference for audit; the field stays. New
 *     writes can no longer reference it because the batch entity type
 *     would also be gone, but that's a deliberate deferred concern, not
 *     something this hook addresses.
 *
 *   In short: nothing this hook would do is correct. Leaving it empty
 *   is the deliberate choice.
 */

/**
 * Implements hook_install().
 */
function supplier_price_ingest_install(): void {
  // Intentionally empty — see file-level doc comment.
}

/**
 * Implements hook_uninstall().
 */
function supplier_price_ingest_uninstall(): void {
  // Intentionally empty — see file-level doc comment.
}
